7:
Seriously, what'd he do to these
guys?
17:
Uh-huh... Well, I guess things just got
a lot more complicated.
28:
So what the hell is this Royal Key
anyway? It seriously messed with
those dogfolk.
33:
I think I remember old man Jay
saying something about it and
some crown...
38:
It's a secret relic that the gods gave
to the Whitetail family.
47:
The Crown of the Beast King gives
people wisdom and power, which is
why the lionfolk tried to steal it.
49:
But we only managed to get the key
to it. We kept it hidden this whole
time, even after getting banished...
53: Claw, did you know about this?
58:
I've heard folktales, at best. But I
guess we now have proof it actually
exists.
60:
...The catfolk have a ton of folktales,
and honestly, I bet only the old
Whitetail knew the truth of them all.
64:
Well, we ain't getting anything out of
him since he's buried beneath the
dirt.
66:
Magnos got his hands on the key,
yeah? But where's this crown then?
71:
In a secret Whitetail ruin. My mom
told me where it was, and I bet
Magnos is there now.
76:
Claw, we don't got time to amass
troops. We'll head out first.
81:
The biggest problem now is what to
do about Shuilong...
86:
Is she that much of a pain in the
neck?
91:
That's an understatement. Seriously,
I don't think any of us can win in a
one-on-one with her.
99:
At least she's not the only crazy
martial artist we got around here.
102:
Right? She's on the roof if you wanna
talk with her.
108:
A little cub like you should be in bed
by now. Did you need something?
111:
I should just... leave the rest to you
adults, shouldn't I?
114:
That'd be the right thing to do. Go to
bed and wake up to see everything's
taken care of.
118:
If that's the case, why do you frown
so?
122: It just... doesn't sit right with me.
134:
The one inside you, telling you to do
something. All that's left is to figure
out what that something is.
138:
...No one will ever see him for who he
is, at this rate.
145: You truly are a kind little cub.
147:
However, what if what he needs is
self-reflection? You won't be able to
help him then.
150:
But... you helped me see who I am,
Helga.
154:
My whole world changed. I don't
care what anyone else says—I'd
rather try than just give up!
158:
Hahaha... To raise your hand against
the odds, hm? You sure are brave.
161: All right, Teo. What do you wish to do?
175:
I know what he's going through! It
has to be me to stop him!
179:
Well, what are you waiting for?
Come on.
183:
Didn't I tell you before? They're an
odd bunch.
191:
Ugh, we don't have time to be
standing around. You wanna hash
things out with that guy, yeah?
199:
I'll change this rotten world... I swear
it!
